WEBVTT

01:06.328 --> 01:08.320
How do you miss something this basic?

01:08.320 --> 01:10.932
Even a newbie wouldn't screw that up.
Are you not nervous?

01:10.932 --> 01:14.602
A company's order is built on rank.

01:18.731 --> 01:21.109
But

01:21.823 --> 01:24.448
their real power struggle

01:24.448 --> 01:26.540
runs deeper

01:26.540 --> 01:29.180
and far more discreet.

01:45.436 --> 01:49.716
Is a perfectly equal relationship
even possible?

01:58.146 --> 02:02.734
The moment two people come together,
a hierarchy forms.

02:04.610 --> 02:07.777
Between friends, between lovers...

02:07.777 --> 02:11.583
there's always an imbalance of power.

02:22.420 --> 02:24.311
And everyone

02:24.311 --> 02:28.311
wants to climb just a little higher.

02:29.535 --> 02:31.199
Even if

02:31.199 --> 02:34.975
it means crossing a line.

02:34.975 --> 02:38.488
This is so good.

02:40.918 --> 02:42.448
What is that?

02:42.448 --> 02:45.118
What?

02:45.118 --> 02:46.319
See? Something's floating.

02:46.319 --> 02:47.554
Where?

02:55.745 --> 02:59.499
You look great on camera, Director Kang.

03:08.341 --> 03:09.900
Are you police?

03:09.900 --> 03:11.593
No, I'm not.

03:13.367 --> 03:15.700
I'm...

03:49.465 --> 03:50.899
[Noh Ki Jun]

03:52.722 --> 03:55.142
From the headquarters audit team.

03:55.142 --> 03:58.180
Stop what you're doing and come talk to me,

03:58.180 --> 04:00.179
Director Kang.

04:02.437 --> 04:04.755
[Interview Room]
[Under Audit]

04:14.785 --> 04:19.984
I heard your audit team could
bring down anyone.

04:20.679 --> 04:22.322
Now you've got people flying, too?

04:22.322 --> 04:24.196
You're the one who's about to fall.

04:24.196 --> 04:26.627
- Hey!
- I'm Noh Ki Jun from Audit Team 1.

04:26.627 --> 04:29.350
You've got some nerve
talking to a director like that.

04:29.350 --> 04:32.441
Who do you think you are, cops? The NIS?

04:32.441 --> 04:35.018
This is illegal filming.

04:35.018 --> 04:40.207
I'll sue all of you for invasion of privacy.

04:42.032 --> 04:46.416
To catch a spy leaking core tech overseas,

04:46.416 --> 04:48.660
this is what it takes.

04:48.660 --> 04:50.684
We've got our reasons too.

04:50.684 --> 04:53.686
People like that love to cry privacy,

04:53.686 --> 04:57.599
but have zero sense of ethics.

04:59.361 --> 05:01.634
Hey.

05:01.634 --> 05:03.769
Take it down a notch.

05:03.769 --> 05:07.255
Even if I were an industrial spy,
it's a first offense.

05:07.255 --> 05:12.102
Act a little sorry, you'll get probation.

05:17.409 --> 05:18.679
Director Kang,

05:18.679 --> 05:20.260
he speaks Korean pretty well, right?

05:20.260 --> 05:21.743
Yeah, he's Korean-Chinese.

05:21.743 --> 05:24.249
Korean, sure.

05:24.249 --> 05:28.042
North Korean.

05:32.610 --> 05:35.788
This company's been funding them.

05:35.788 --> 05:38.708
It's disguised as foreign trade,

05:38.708 --> 05:42.408
but it's all run by the North.

05:46.249 --> 05:50.598
If espionage charges apply,

05:50.598 --> 05:54.444
then you're not just an industrial spy.
You're the real deal.

05:54.444 --> 05:57.552
Probation?

05:57.552 --> 06:01.181
You'll be doing time.

06:11.440 --> 06:16.366
[Interview Room]
[Under Audit]

06:16.366 --> 06:19.635
You idiots. I told you, it's not me.
Why won't you believe me?

06:19.635 --> 06:22.107
- Sir, please calm down.
- "Calm down?"

06:22.107 --> 06:24.712
- We got a report.
- A report? What report?

06:24.712 --> 06:26.778
It's all made up. Total setup.

06:26.778 --> 06:30.124
Team 3 never has a quiet day.

06:30.124 --> 06:31.863
What is it this time?

06:31.863 --> 06:34.340
A report says that general manager lied

06:34.340 --> 06:36.549
about being married and hit on her.

06:36.549 --> 06:39.553
She said there's a mole as proof.

06:39.553 --> 06:40.983
- What?
- Down there.

06:40.983 --> 06:43.073
There.

06:45.617 --> 06:48.940
Haemu Group. 7th in the conglomerate rankings.

06:48.940 --> 06:50.525
[Haemu Group]
9th in revenue.

06:50.525 --> 06:54.937
This conglomerate, with 42 affiliates,
has its top department.

06:54.937 --> 06:56.741
[Audit Office]
Even within the audit office,

06:56.741 --> 07:00.044
[Audit Team 1, 2, 3]
there's a clear hierarchy.

07:00.044 --> 07:01.901
Teams 1 and 2

07:01.901 --> 07:05.894
handle major cases, like embezzlement,
breach of trust,

07:05.894 --> 07:09.737
collusion, and data leaks.

07:09.737 --> 07:12.543
As for Team 3...

07:13.201 --> 07:16.205
- Alright, let go.
- Yeah.

07:16.205 --> 07:18.971
I'll show you.

07:21.113 --> 07:23.609
No, don't! Stop!

07:25.312 --> 07:27.269
Seriously...

07:27.269 --> 07:29.498
Look closely.

07:29.498 --> 07:33.652
- See it? A mole?
- Hey, don't cover it.

07:33.652 --> 07:38.131
Yeah... they do this kind of thing.

07:40.196 --> 07:45.617
[Episode 1: Up, Down, Up-Up, Down]

08:18.223 --> 08:21.212
- Good morning.
- Morning.

08:21.212 --> 08:23.489
Hey, Mr. Gentleman Noh Ki Jun.

08:23.489 --> 08:26.242
Looking sharp as always.

08:26.242 --> 08:29.746
Thanks. Let's have a good one.

08:47.736 --> 08:50.114
[Protecting core tech from industrial spies]

08:50.114 --> 08:52.275
[Haemu Audit Office]

08:52.275 --> 08:55.245
[Noh Ki Jun, Audit Team 1]
Auditing is about improving operations

08:55.245 --> 08:58.709
and adding value.

08:58.709 --> 09:01.556
[Audit's Smile Angel]
[Noh Ki Jun, Audit Team 1]

09:05.709 --> 09:08.326
"Smile angel?" Since when is audit an angel?

09:08.326 --> 09:10.823
Hey, I didn't make that up.

09:10.823 --> 09:12.710
Why not? I'd be proud.

09:12.710 --> 09:16.060
He's the face of audit.

09:16.060 --> 09:18.957
Honestly, yesterday was embarrassing.

09:18.957 --> 09:21.088
What was that naked show?

09:21.088 --> 09:23.149
Total chaos yesterday.

09:23.149 --> 09:26.913
I even dreamed about it.
The general manager's... you know.

09:26.913 --> 09:29.713
- Man...
- No way.

09:32.430 --> 09:35.528
- This is just kimbap.
- Sorry, sorry.

09:35.528 --> 09:39.458
But why do we even handle stuff like that?
It's not exactly classy.

09:39.458 --> 09:41.322
If there's a report, we have to deal with it.

09:41.322 --> 09:43.346
That's what Team 3 is for.

09:43.346 --> 09:47.401
Teams 1 and 2 handle the big stuff,
and dump the rest on them.

09:47.401 --> 09:51.743
They stake out for attendance checks,
time bathroom breaks, even smoking breaks.

09:51.743 --> 09:56.459
I saw them going around
counting coffee sticks in every break room.

09:56.459 --> 09:58.253
Man, that's depressing.

09:58.253 --> 10:01.815
They say the HQ Audit can take down anyone.

10:01.815 --> 10:04.600
- But Team 3...
- It's more like...

10:04.600 --> 10:07.357
they clean up bird crap.

10:07.357 --> 10:09.983
In short, the bird poop team.

10:11.388 --> 10:13.498
Don't let anyone hear that.

10:13.498 --> 10:15.921
Oh, it's Secretary Park.

10:23.275 --> 10:26.821
Good morning. Nice weather, huh?

10:27.812 --> 10:30.166
Yeah.

10:30.166 --> 10:32.069
Starting the day seeing her?

10:32.069 --> 10:34.840
That's a good sign, right?

10:34.840 --> 10:37.679
I'll head up first. Finish up and come up.

10:37.679 --> 10:40.173
Already?

11:00.354 --> 11:02.649
What's my schedule this afternoon?

11:02.649 --> 11:06.529
You have a meeting
with Haemu Media executives.

11:13.909 --> 11:16.746
Nice tie.

11:21.428 --> 11:25.021
Thank you, sir. You've got great taste.

11:59.961 --> 12:03.060
- Hey.
- Hi.

12:17.092 --> 12:18.635
Oh, right.

12:18.635 --> 12:23.329
Everyone saw you on the company broadcast.
They're all asking who the hot guy is.

12:23.329 --> 12:26.682
Yeah?
They'll lose it when they see me in person.

12:26.682 --> 12:29.279
What are you doing after work?

12:29.279 --> 12:33.339
Want to grab a drink?
There's a nice wine bar nearby.

12:33.339 --> 12:37.212
- Where?
- It's called...

12:46.330 --> 12:48.128
Let's talk later, okay?

12:48.128 --> 12:50.673
Ki Jun!

13:00.225 --> 13:03.395
Just a moment. Hey!

13:08.627 --> 13:10.808
Ji Hye.

13:12.455 --> 13:16.298
That's quite a greeting.

13:16.298 --> 13:18.842
I missed you.

13:18.842 --> 13:23.302
You meeting her tonight?
Hang out with me instead.

13:24.091 --> 13:25.627
Wait.

13:29.331 --> 13:31.875
Aren't you getting married?

13:31.875 --> 13:32.924
Called it off?

13:32.924 --> 13:34.866
No, but...

13:34.866 --> 13:37.005
I've been feeling down.

13:37.005 --> 13:41.998
The thought of being with one man forever...

13:43.287 --> 13:45.597
Can we

13:45.597 --> 13:49.943
have one last night?

13:55.396 --> 13:58.468
I'm not that kind of guy.

14:06.249 --> 14:10.527
Pre-wedding jitters are normal.

14:10.527 --> 14:12.864
I'll make it up to you

14:12.864 --> 14:15.993
with a generous wedding gift.

14:15.993 --> 14:17.678
Oh please.

14:17.678 --> 14:20.181
How generous?

14:26.079 --> 14:28.525
Wait.

14:47.164 --> 14:48.194
What are you doing?

14:48.194 --> 14:49.938
Hey, Ki Jun.

14:49.938 --> 14:51.375
Look, it's blooming.

14:51.375 --> 14:53.848
Who's been watering this thing?

14:53.848 --> 14:56.654
Pretty impressive for this dull office.

14:56.654 --> 14:58.787
You're getting sentimental.

14:58.787 --> 15:03.322
Not like you'd care. Your life's in full bloom.

15:03.322 --> 15:06.199
I heard from HR just now.

15:06.199 --> 15:08.616
Something about a promotion
after the Director Kang case.

15:08.616 --> 15:10.016
That true?

15:11.025 --> 15:14.930
- I don't know.
- Come on. Must be true, huh?

15:14.930 --> 15:19.765
Executive Kim really backed you, didn't he?

15:20.883 --> 15:25.413
I got on your side early. Don't forget that.

15:25.413 --> 15:27.097
Guys!

15:27.097 --> 15:28.803
Did you hear?

15:28.803 --> 15:29.832
What?

15:29.832 --> 15:33.200
The whole company's on edge.
There's this scary rumor going around.

15:33.200 --> 15:34.874
It's serious.

15:34.874 --> 15:36.832
What is it?

15:37.920 --> 15:39.905
She's coming back,

15:39.905 --> 15:42.333
Joo In Ah.

15:48.085 --> 15:49.153
[New message received]

15:49.153 --> 15:50.342
[Class of '19 Group Chat]
Isn't that Joo In Ah?

15:50.342 --> 15:52.341
[Class of '22 Group Chat]
It's Joo In Ah.

15:52.341 --> 15:54.848
[I'm already stressed...]
[No way]

15:58.813 --> 16:00.050
She's here.

16:00.050 --> 16:02.303
- We're screwed...
- Is she back for good?

16:02.303 --> 16:04.370
- Might be time to quit.
- Why'd she come back?

16:04.370 --> 16:06.577
- I'm already stressed...
- Too many CCs are the worst.

16:06.577 --> 16:11.373
[Will this affect overseas too?]
[Even the field teams are on edge]

16:11.373 --> 16:13.295
Watch out

16:13.295 --> 16:16.121
for people with nicknames.

16:16.121 --> 16:20.507
They're made for easy trash talk.

16:20.507 --> 16:23.724
Joo In Ah probably has

16:23.724 --> 16:25.888
a dozen.

16:25.888 --> 16:28.964
You know "Joo In Ah-out?"

16:28.964 --> 16:32.969
If she targets you, you're out.

16:32.969 --> 16:35.771
My favorite's this one. "Office ghost."

16:35.771 --> 16:40.741
She practically lives here, day and night.

16:40.741 --> 16:43.947
She picked up another nickname overseas.

16:43.947 --> 16:44.972
What is it?

16:44.972 --> 16:48.938
She got into it with a gang
over business rights.

16:49.936 --> 16:52.705
So now

16:52.705 --> 16:55.219
it's "Joo Sniper."

16:55.219 --> 16:57.323
Wait, she actually shot someone?

16:57.323 --> 16:58.567
Probably just a rumor.

16:58.567 --> 17:01.367
How does a rumor get that crazy?

17:01.367 --> 17:04.133
What matters is

17:04.133 --> 17:06.964
which team she joins.

17:06.964 --> 17:08.953
Right?

17:22.445 --> 17:26.172
[Kim Jin Hee, Planning Team:
She got on the elevator]

17:26.992 --> 17:30.865
- Joo In Ah just got on the elevator.
- Which floor did she press?

17:36.842 --> 17:38.932
He says she's smashing every button.

17:38.932 --> 17:43.613
Man, my heart's about to burst.

17:43.613 --> 17:45.993
Passed 4F.

17:47.332 --> 17:48.812
And 5F...

17:48.812 --> 17:51.950
Passed 6F!

17:53.605 --> 17:55.477
Where is she even going?

17:55.477 --> 17:57.939
- Did HR post anything?
- Not yet.

17:57.939 --> 17:59.837
[HR & Information Office]

18:00.608 --> 18:03.149
[Bu Se Yeong, Head of HR]

18:10.910 --> 18:12.648
[Request for HR Transfer Approval]

18:12.648 --> 18:15.564
[Cancel] [Confirm]

18:17.565 --> 18:20.112
9F.

18:21.171 --> 18:22.943
[Please don't stop at 14...]
10F.

18:22.943 --> 18:25.179
[Please...]
Why does she keep coming up?

18:25.179 --> 18:27.204
[Just don't get off on my floor]
[Keep going, please]

18:27.204 --> 18:29.481
[Please get off...]
[Why is this elevator so slow today?]

18:31.431 --> 18:33.309
[I'm getting off first]
[Lucky you]

18:35.185 --> 18:37.812
[Passed 13 for now]
[Is this the stop?]

18:37.812 --> 18:39.395
[14F]

19:08.270 --> 19:11.070
14F!

19:16.976 --> 19:18.894
[Planning, Audit Office]

19:18.894 --> 19:20.479
Stay calm!

19:20.479 --> 19:23.982
Planning's on 14 too.

19:23.982 --> 19:25.496
[Planning Office]

19:25.496 --> 19:27.527
Hey, clean over there too!

19:27.527 --> 19:29.554
Hurry! Hurry!

19:29.554 --> 19:31.579
All that scrap paper and coffee on your desk!

19:31.579 --> 19:35.684
Finish it and toss it, now!

20:00.143 --> 20:02.227
Mr. Kim Gyu Young?

20:16.653 --> 20:18.077
Nice to meet you.

20:18.077 --> 20:21.897
I'm Joo In Ah, your new Head of Audit.

20:27.989 --> 20:31.353
What is this? Why's it so gloomy in here?

20:31.353 --> 20:33.880
Should I sing something?

20:40.132 --> 20:44.089
Thanks for the warm welcome.

20:44.089 --> 20:45.685
Nice to meet you.

20:45.685 --> 20:47.941
Manager Kwon Myung Jin.

20:47.941 --> 20:49.331
Nice to meet you.

20:49.331 --> 20:51.421
You look thrilled. Relax.

20:51.421 --> 20:52.955
Oh, sorry.

20:52.955 --> 20:55.512
Moon Kyung Jin, Deputy Manager, Audit Team 1.

20:55.512 --> 20:57.125
Deputy Manager?

20:57.125 --> 21:00.382
You look so young. Nice to meet you.

21:00.382 --> 21:03.313
Kim Tae Hwan, Team Leader of Audit Team 2.
Nice to meet you.

21:03.313 --> 21:06.408
I should be saying that. Thank you.

21:06.408 --> 21:09.087
Jung Dong Min, Deputy Manager, Team 2.

21:09.087 --> 21:10.668
Nice to meet you.

21:10.668 --> 21:13.925
Joo Yeon Woo, Senior Staff of Team 1.

21:13.925 --> 21:17.848
We share the same last name.

21:17.848 --> 21:21.774
- It's a pretty great one.
- That's right.

21:22.476 --> 21:24.227
Nice to meet you.

21:24.227 --> 21:26.605
She's more normal than I thought.

21:26.605 --> 21:28.418
Guess the rumors weren't true.

21:28.418 --> 21:32.357
Yeah, I got worked up for nothing.

21:32.357 --> 21:35.741
Hello, I'm Sung Doo Gi, Senior Staff of Team 1.

21:35.741 --> 21:36.896
Nice to meet you.

21:36.896 --> 21:38.366
I like the energy.

21:38.366 --> 21:39.431
Keep it up.

21:39.431 --> 21:40.480
Thank you.

21:40.480 --> 21:44.332
Ahn Min Soo, Assistant Manager, same team.
Go easy on me.

21:44.332 --> 21:46.235
I'll expect you to be charming.

21:46.235 --> 21:48.179
Yes.

21:50.668 --> 21:53.745
Hello, I'm Noh Ki Jun,
Assistant Manager, Team 1.

21:55.881 --> 21:58.336
Assistant Manager Noh Ki Jun?

22:13.631 --> 22:15.766
Let's get to work.

22:24.568 --> 22:25.899
Excuse me.

22:25.899 --> 22:27.999
Could you take a look?

22:27.999 --> 22:30.880
No problem. Let me see.

22:35.769 --> 22:40.947
It's the routine audit notice.
Needs your approval right away.

22:40.947 --> 22:42.484
Haemu Industries.

22:42.484 --> 22:44.010
Five years in a row?

22:44.010 --> 22:45.604
Yeah, right.

22:45.604 --> 22:49.366
I've handled it ever since I transferred here
from Haemu Industries.

22:49.366 --> 22:53.011
So you've been auditing your old team
for five years.

22:53.011 --> 22:54.030
[Routine Audit Notice]

22:54.625 --> 22:58.175
That's enough. Time to move on.

22:58.175 --> 23:01.919
Same affiliate, two years max.
That's the rule now.

23:01.919 --> 23:05.072
One year for former teams.

23:07.609 --> 23:11.902
I get what you're saying,

23:11.902 --> 23:15.106
but I know that place best.

23:15.106 --> 23:19.027
I know exactly where the problems are.

23:19.027 --> 23:23.643
How rotten is it
that you couldn't dig it up in five years?

23:28.073 --> 23:30.024
Oh, come on.

23:30.024 --> 23:33.277
- It's just...
- You smiling?

23:43.926 --> 23:46.624
If I say don't go,

23:46.624 --> 23:49.155
then don't go.

23:49.155 --> 23:50.963
Why nitpick every little thing?

23:50.963 --> 23:55.183
You think I'm here to debate you?

23:55.183 --> 23:57.986
If you knew that place so well,

23:57.986 --> 24:00.293
why'd you just skim the surface?

24:00.293 --> 24:03.310
Not a single major disciplinary case.

24:03.310 --> 24:07.463
Hard to go after your old buddies?

24:07.463 --> 24:09.351
No, that's not it.

24:09.351 --> 24:12.991
Or were you in on it?
Got something tucked away?

24:12.991 --> 24:14.535
Should I dig into it?

24:14.535 --> 24:17.134
Were you auditing or doing business?

24:17.134 --> 24:18.860
How could you say that...

24:18.860 --> 24:20.791
Then what is it?

24:20.791 --> 24:24.115
You just don't respect your new boss, huh?

24:24.115 --> 24:27.370
I'm sorry.

24:40.965 --> 24:43.803
Guess no one's that busy.

24:47.762 --> 24:49.153
So...

24:49.153 --> 24:51.703
we'll start one-on-ones now.

24:51.703 --> 24:55.469
When I call your name, come in.

25:03.409 --> 25:05.582
[Cost of opening a chicken shop]

25:05.582 --> 25:08.091
[Should I quit...]

25:08.091 --> 25:10.513
[I want to cry]

25:10.513 --> 25:12.885
[Interview Room]

25:23.133 --> 25:26.179
Manager Ha Jin Woo, Team 2.

25:35.276 --> 25:39.163
This place turned into Jurassic Park fast.

25:39.163 --> 25:41.059
Hey, can you even work like this?

25:41.059 --> 25:42.100
Well...

25:42.100 --> 25:44.677
She didn't say anything wrong.

25:44.677 --> 25:46.701
Guess high performers think alike.

25:46.701 --> 25:49.255
Heard she got promoted three times too.

25:50.694 --> 25:54.061
Hey, you heading to Haemu Pharma again?

25:54.061 --> 25:56.145
What is it this time?

25:56.145 --> 25:59.604
Something shady over there?

25:59.604 --> 26:05.254
I'll tell you when it's ready.

26:05.254 --> 26:09.328
Man, you promotion junkies...

26:17.645 --> 26:19.731
Please get him a glass of water.

26:19.731 --> 26:21.165
Yes.

26:23.533 --> 26:26.220
I'm screwed.

26:36.210 --> 26:38.771
Assistant Manager Noh Ki Jun, Team 1.

26:40.004 --> 26:41.638
Yes.

26:47.334 --> 26:50.264
Each interview will be capped at three minutes.

26:50.264 --> 26:54.416
Yes, I'm all for efficient meetings.

26:54.416 --> 26:57.267
Alright, Assistant Manager Noh Ki Jun.

26:57.267 --> 26:59.229
[Performance Evaluation Sheet]
Excellent reviews.

26:59.229 --> 27:02.035
Straight S ratings since you joined.

27:02.035 --> 27:03.113
I've been lucky.

27:03.113 --> 27:05.398
So it was luck.

27:07.889 --> 27:11.735
You've handled major cases
across key affiliates.

27:11.735 --> 27:13.859
Quite a track record.

27:13.859 --> 27:15.883
I worked hard

27:15.883 --> 27:18.164
to make that luck happen.

27:18.164 --> 27:21.844
Okay. Let's adjust your position.

27:21.844 --> 27:23.669
A promotion?

27:23.669 --> 27:25.314
Already?

27:25.314 --> 27:28.991
- But it's not review season yet.
- Doesn't matter.

27:28.991 --> 27:31.435
If that's your call, I appreciate...

27:31.435 --> 27:33.625
You're moving to Team 3.

27:33.625 --> 27:34.885
Sorry? Team 3?

27:34.885 --> 27:37.929
You'll handle PM cases there.

27:37.929 --> 27:39.269
PM in Audit means...

27:39.269 --> 27:40.473
"Public Morals."

27:40.473 --> 27:42.677
"P" from Public, "M" from Morals.

27:42.677 --> 27:45.500
Mostly office affairs.

27:45.500 --> 27:48.537
You want me handling affairs?

27:48.537 --> 27:50.257
Yes.

27:52.730 --> 27:54.281
So...

27:54.281 --> 27:57.481
You start today.

28:04.421 --> 28:05.698
Excuse me.

28:05.698 --> 28:07.895
Why am I being assigned to PM in Team 3?

28:07.895 --> 28:09.918
I just don't get it.

28:09.918 --> 28:12.028
Why should I have to convince you?

28:12.028 --> 28:14.448
- I'm exercising my authority.
- Right.

28:14.448 --> 28:17.548
But you said it yourself.
My evaluations are all strong.

28:19.328 --> 28:22.065
Good job.

28:23.492 --> 28:24.990
Our team?

28:24.990 --> 28:26.924
I was going to tell you later, but

28:26.924 --> 28:31.784
there's an Audit I've been leading in Team 1.
A key affiliate case.

28:31.784 --> 28:33.228
Let me finish it.

28:33.228 --> 28:35.321
Upload everything to the team cloud.

28:35.321 --> 28:37.698
I'll review and reassign it.

28:37.698 --> 28:40.475
The logic's complex,
and it involves key personnel.

28:40.475 --> 28:44.127
It needs a subtle approach.

28:44.127 --> 28:47.074
The person who can close this?

28:48.054 --> 28:50.987
That's me.

29:09.583 --> 29:11.769
That's funny.

29:13.370 --> 29:14.584
Hey.

29:14.584 --> 29:17.290
What makes you so special? Got superpowers?

29:17.290 --> 29:18.933
Can you fly? Teleport?

29:18.933 --> 29:20.840
Shoot energy blasts?

29:20.840 --> 29:26.434
Who do you think you are?
You really believe only you can do this job?

29:26.434 --> 29:27.989
Don't tell me

29:27.989 --> 29:31.266
you think you're irreplaceable.

29:31.266 --> 29:33.716
Phones sell just fine without Steve Jobs.

29:33.716 --> 29:37.905
You think
Haemu Audit Team 1 stops without you?

29:38.577 --> 29:41.174
How can you be this naive?

29:41.174 --> 29:43.114
Fine, think what you want.

29:43.114 --> 29:47.038
But saying it to my face?

29:47.038 --> 29:49.624
That's bold.

29:51.829 --> 29:56.616
I'll let it slide this time.
Don't waste my time again.

29:58.383 --> 30:01.520
At least tell me why.

30:01.520 --> 30:06.328
There must be a reason you picked me for PM.

30:06.328 --> 30:10.194
Because you're...

30:11.727 --> 30:13.943
perfect for it.

30:21.693 --> 30:23.830
Hey, what happened?

30:23.830 --> 30:25.680
I thought you were getting promoted.

30:25.680 --> 30:29.601
Promotion? This is a demotion.

30:29.601 --> 30:32.540
Team 3, and PM?

30:32.540 --> 30:35.705
But they're nice people.

30:35.705 --> 30:40.457
Right, yeah. They seem really nice.

30:40.457 --> 30:43.143
Just help them out.

30:45.342 --> 30:48.099
Help them out. They seem nice.

30:48.099 --> 30:50.372
Do your best.

30:55.051 --> 30:58.879
It's Audit's ace, Assistant Manager Noh Ki Jun!

30:58.879 --> 31:00.191
Welcome.

31:00.191 --> 31:02.261
How old are you again?

31:02.261 --> 31:04.615
Not married yet, right? Or couldn't?

31:04.615 --> 31:06.725
Team Leader Moo Gwang Il,

31:06.725 --> 31:08.052
Audit's official "gave up on promotion."

31:08.052 --> 31:10.882
[Too much talker / Married]
You know, being single's the trend these days.

31:10.882 --> 31:15.058
Think of it as a welcome kit.
Go ahead, check it.

31:15.058 --> 31:18.043
Pyeon Hae Young, the team's backbone
who runs the office.

31:18.043 --> 31:19.385
[Strict at work / Single]

31:19.385 --> 31:21.488
Everything you need should be in there.

31:21.488 --> 31:25.888
It's usually two pens, but I added one more.

31:25.888 --> 31:31.005
If you need more,
write your name, sign, and take it.

31:31.005 --> 31:33.695
For a big company like Haemu,
this feels a bit cheap.

31:33.695 --> 31:37.940
Take it up with him.

31:37.940 --> 31:41.583
All I did was grab a battery once.
She's too much.

31:41.583 --> 31:44.033
You took the whole pack.

31:44.033 --> 31:47.886
AA and AAA, two packs.

31:47.886 --> 31:51.524
Manager Cha Seong Tae,
always looking for something to pocket.

31:51.524 --> 31:53.621
[Meju Market rating 78.8° / Married]
Seriously...

31:53.621 --> 31:54.746
Excuse me, sir.

31:54.746 --> 31:57.147
Welcome to Team 3.

31:57.147 --> 32:00.784
If you need anything, just let me know anytime.

32:00.784 --> 32:02.928
Baek Hyun Gyu, the self-appointed fixer.

32:02.928 --> 32:04.687
[Grateful for audit work / Single]
They call him White Blood Cell.

32:04.687 --> 32:09.323
Let me adjust your chair before you sit.

32:18.308 --> 32:19.479
Wait,

32:19.479 --> 32:21.784
[Can't hear you / Single]
wasn't Yoon Da Ye here?

32:21.784 --> 32:26.511
Seoul National, CPA, insane resume.

32:26.511 --> 32:29.945
Hello, Assistant Manager Yoon.

32:29.945 --> 32:32.122
She's MZ.

32:32.122 --> 32:35.135
You know, MZ?

32:41.518 --> 32:46.129
How is this team supposed to work?

32:46.129 --> 32:48.748
Damn it.

32:48.748 --> 32:50.593
I can't believe...

32:50.593 --> 32:52.490
I can't believe

32:52.490 --> 32:56.549
I'm stuck with them.

33:20.580 --> 33:23.986
Already time for him to get off work.

33:27.120 --> 33:30.140
Is he late again?

33:32.332 --> 33:33.888
[Honey]

33:40.646 --> 33:45.758
Your call can't be completed.
You'll be charged after the beep.

33:56.698 --> 33:58.021
Yes.

33:58.021 --> 34:00.178
Got it.

34:00.178 --> 34:02.156
- What did they say?
- Spoke to the vendor.

34:02.156 --> 34:04.020
They'll meet the deadline.

34:04.020 --> 34:05.432
Nice, well done.

34:05.432 --> 34:07.576
You're really good at this.

34:07.576 --> 34:10.120
Learned from the best.

34:10.120 --> 34:12.265
Hey, your phone's ringing.

34:15.112 --> 34:17.276
Hey, honey.

34:17.276 --> 34:20.916
Did I not tell you? We've got a team dinner.

34:21.575 --> 34:23.419
Another one?

34:23.419 --> 34:24.988
Yeah, sorry. It's been hectic.

34:24.988 --> 34:26.736
Hello, ma'am.

34:26.736 --> 34:29.353
This is Deputy Manager Jung Mi Yeong.

34:29.353 --> 34:31.533
Oh, hello.

34:31.533 --> 34:35.310
Hard to see your husband these days, right?
The TF's been intense.

34:35.310 --> 34:39.997
I'll try to send him home early.

34:39.997 --> 34:42.383
I'll be home early. Sorry.

34:42.383 --> 34:45.462
Okay. Don't be too late.

34:59.521 --> 35:04.401
Who does she think she is,
sending my husband home?

35:10.639 --> 35:13.718
Who does she think she is?

35:19.272 --> 35:22.418
Damn it!

35:25.851 --> 35:27.321
So...

35:27.321 --> 35:29.828
this is the hotline desk.

35:29.828 --> 35:34.564
We get a lot of tips. Just answer and log them.

35:36.134 --> 35:37.303
Got it.

35:37.303 --> 35:38.854
Yeah.

35:48.484 --> 35:51.021
Hello, Audit Team 1...

35:51.021 --> 35:52.504
No, I mean Team 3.

35:52.504 --> 35:53.941
Hello.

35:53.941 --> 35:56.324
This is a bit awkward, but...

35:56.324 --> 36:00.184
It's about our team leader.

36:00.184 --> 36:01.881
Yes.

36:01.881 --> 36:04.174
Are you reporting an internal issue?

36:04.174 --> 36:07.731
He keeps farting in the office.

36:07.731 --> 36:09.215
It's really bad.

36:09.215 --> 36:12.261
All day, nonstop. The air's unbearable.

36:12.261 --> 36:16.027
At least get us an air purifier.

36:18.244 --> 36:21.224
Oh, I see.

36:33.658 --> 36:35.434
Hello, this is...

36:35.434 --> 36:38.751
Hey, you bastard! Why'd you pick up so late?

36:38.751 --> 36:41.481
You get paid for this, don't you? Shit.

36:41.481 --> 36:43.451
- This is Audit.
- What?

36:43.451 --> 36:47.264
Your company needs to crash for you to wake up.

36:47.264 --> 36:49.154
Yeah.

36:49.154 --> 36:50.901
- What would you like to report?
- Report?

36:50.901 --> 36:53.231
I'm reporting your life, you idiot.
What's your name?

36:53.231 --> 36:55.924
I'll tell your chairman myself.

36:55.924 --> 37:00.104
What's your name? Damn it!

37:03.960 --> 37:05.584
What is this?

37:05.584 --> 37:07.654
It's proof of an affair.

37:07.654 --> 37:11.247
I dug it out of the trash.

37:11.247 --> 37:14.140
So what is this...

37:21.183 --> 37:24.230
Hey, where are you going?

38:02.956 --> 38:05.615
Ki Jun, you okay?

38:05.615 --> 38:08.729
You looked pale going in.

38:08.729 --> 38:11.046
Want someone to pat your back?

38:11.046 --> 38:14.341
Or should I come in?

38:24.188 --> 38:26.201
I'm fine.

38:28.055 --> 38:30.352
You sure?

38:30.352 --> 38:33.716
If it's too much, take a break.

38:33.716 --> 38:37.209
You know, health comes first.

38:48.172 --> 38:51.023
Let's make the formal introductions.

38:51.023 --> 38:54.299
This is Joo In Ah, our new Head of Audit.

38:55.144 --> 38:59.400
And Executive Kim Han Soo,
former Head of Audit, now Head of Strategy.

38:59.400 --> 39:01.580
I've heard a lot about you.

39:01.580 --> 39:04.213
Congratulations on the promotion.

39:04.213 --> 39:06.456
Head of HR, Bu Se Yeong.

39:06.456 --> 39:09.104
In Ah, long time.

39:09.920 --> 39:13.532
We used to be on the same team.

39:13.532 --> 39:17.184
I was her senior.

39:17.184 --> 39:18.921
Se Yeong.

39:18.921 --> 39:20.945
You look great.

39:20.945 --> 39:22.909
HR must suit you.

39:25.992 --> 39:30.513
You two seem close. Great to see.

39:30.513 --> 39:34.906
This appointment was a brilliant move.

39:34.906 --> 39:38.323
Audit is the company's blade,

39:38.323 --> 39:41.923
serving the Vice Chairman and the Chairman.

39:41.923 --> 39:45.380
Someone like you fits perfectly.

39:45.380 --> 39:48.329
Oh, you knew it.

39:49.564 --> 39:51.721
I'm pretty good with a blade.

39:54.253 --> 39:57.069
Yeah, she has a sharp wit.

39:57.069 --> 39:59.596
You guys will get used to it.

40:01.146 --> 40:03.178
How does it feel to be back in Seoul?

40:03.178 --> 40:05.370
Air's the same everywhere.

40:06.053 --> 40:09.040
Maybe a bit more polluted here.

40:09.040 --> 40:10.651
So...

40:11.813 --> 40:14.893
Any regrets about coming back?

40:22.448 --> 40:24.323
If I did,

40:24.323 --> 40:28.009
could I go back?

40:44.345 --> 40:46.217
Time flies.

40:46.217 --> 40:47.977
Shall we get dinner?

40:47.977 --> 40:50.936
I still have a lot to review.

40:50.936 --> 40:52.754
Rain check.

40:52.754 --> 40:54.114
Next time, let's grab some steak.

40:54.114 --> 40:55.808
Of course.

40:57.077 --> 40:58.714
What about you, Vice Chairman?

40:58.714 --> 41:00.948
I'm having dinner at home tonight.

41:00.948 --> 41:03.021
My wife's probably already there.

41:03.021 --> 41:04.939
See?

41:04.939 --> 41:08.118
He's a total family man.

41:08.118 --> 41:10.849
How's the Chairman doing?

41:10.849 --> 41:14.459
He was discharged last week.
We're keeping an eye on him.

41:15.818 --> 41:19.091
I check on him regularly.

42:15.897 --> 42:18.847
Your call can't be completed.

42:26.105 --> 42:28.929
Your call can't be completed.

42:34.243 --> 42:36.525
Why aren't you answering?

42:36.525 --> 42:38.775
Call me. Why won't you pick up?

42:38.775 --> 42:40.711
Call me. Still at the dinner?

42:40.711 --> 42:42.924
When are you coming home?

42:48.802 --> 42:50.417
It sucks.

42:58.912 --> 43:00.830
Alright, our dream team,

43:00.830 --> 43:03.736
Deputy Manager Son

43:03.736 --> 43:06.097
and Deputy Manager Jung.

43:08.402 --> 43:12.129
This brand launch is make-or-break
for Haemu Food Division.

43:12.129 --> 43:12.997
Yeah.

43:12.997 --> 43:15.523
You two need to create maximum synergy.

43:15.523 --> 43:17.353
- Yes, sir.
- We'll do our best.

43:17.353 --> 43:18.980
- You sure?
- We'll give it our all.

43:18.980 --> 43:20.518
Alright, cheers.

43:20.518 --> 43:22.205
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

43:22.205 --> 43:24.863
- Let's go for it.
- Let's do it.

43:30.709 --> 43:33.709
- You drank yesterday too?
- Yeah...

43:44.141 --> 43:49.468
Your call can't be completed.
You'll be charged after the beep.

44:09.842 --> 44:11.771
Honey!

44:15.599 --> 44:17.521
Sorry.

44:35.549 --> 44:37.932
Your call can't be completed...

45:23.230 --> 45:24.847
Damn it! Open the door!

45:24.847 --> 45:27.161
Hey, open up!

45:27.161 --> 45:28.946
Open it or I'll kill you!

45:28.946 --> 45:30.630
Open the door!

45:30.630 --> 45:32.882
- Hey!
- Honey?

45:35.812 --> 45:37.750
What are you doing?

46:04.611 --> 46:06.274
Heading out already?

46:10.568 --> 46:13.245
Why does he look so out of it?

46:13.245 --> 46:15.961
He has changed in half a day.

46:50.797 --> 46:53.146
[Waiting anxiously for the results]

46:53.146 --> 46:57.012
[Jung Sang Hyun]
[2-star to 1-star demotion]

46:58.332 --> 47:02.880
The verse lacked precision...

47:04.059 --> 47:07.880
There's no such thing as a permanent hierarchy.

47:09.062 --> 47:10.873
That's why

47:12.052 --> 47:14.429
the higher you go,

47:14.429 --> 47:16.451
the more anxious you get.

47:42.474 --> 47:44.139
This is so embarrassing.

47:44.139 --> 47:46.584
How did you even find the place?

47:46.584 --> 47:48.849
Did you go around checking every spot?

47:48.849 --> 47:52.482
- Then why didn't you answer?
- I was at a team dinner!

47:54.387 --> 47:56.837
You couldn't pick up while eating?

47:56.837 --> 47:58.845
What?

47:59.468 --> 48:00.765
Right.

48:00.765 --> 48:04.795
You're always stuck at home.
How would you understand work life?

48:04.795 --> 48:08.556
This is so frustrating.

48:15.435 --> 48:19.252
If you don't want to stay at the bottom,

48:19.252 --> 48:22.540
you have to fight and win.

48:47.899 --> 48:51.242
In the end, holding your rank means

48:51.242 --> 48:54.875
surviving.

49:00.828 --> 49:02.105
Huh?

49:02.105 --> 49:05.422
Why is he eliminated?

49:05.422 --> 49:09.839
He can sing, dance, he's good-looking,
he's got everything.

49:09.839 --> 49:13.296
He's clearly an ace. Why is he out?

49:13.296 --> 49:14.959
Why?

49:14.959 --> 49:17.482
Why?

49:58.535 --> 50:01.562
Ki Jun,

50:01.562 --> 50:04.279
she has a tip for Audit.

50:04.279 --> 50:07.795
She's been waiting since morning.

50:11.285 --> 50:13.689
I think my husband

50:13.689 --> 50:16.339
is having an affair.

50:16.339 --> 50:18.283
Oh my.

50:18.283 --> 50:20.616
When he came home

50:20.616 --> 50:25.006
with perfume as a birthday gift, I just knew.

50:25.006 --> 50:27.872
Perfume?

50:28.692 --> 50:33.363
Who gives perfume to a married man?
What else could it mean?

50:33.363 --> 50:37.393
It's marking territory by scent.

50:37.393 --> 50:41.203
Putting her scent on my man.

50:41.203 --> 50:43.487
After that, I watched him closely.

50:43.487 --> 50:45.864
He never puts his phone down.

50:45.864 --> 50:51.444
He even takes it into the shower.
I read online that means he's cheating.

50:52.468 --> 50:54.625
They're always glued together.

50:54.625 --> 50:58.795
They even travel for work together.
They text late at night.

50:58.795 --> 51:02.381
And I have proof.

51:13.260 --> 51:16.466
That's a hair.

51:17.069 --> 51:20.473
It was on his clothes. It has to be hers.

51:20.473 --> 51:23.386
I'm sure of it.

51:24.033 --> 51:26.138
Ma'am, this isn't really...

51:26.138 --> 51:30.247
We'll look into it and get back to you soon.

51:30.247 --> 51:32.960
Okay.

51:35.771 --> 51:37.557
What?

51:37.557 --> 51:39.980
We got a tip, we follow procedure.

51:39.980 --> 51:43.672
Write a report, interview the parties.

51:43.672 --> 51:47.458
Go check it out. Now.

51:48.707 --> 51:50.824
Check what?

51:50.824 --> 51:54.885
Run a DNA test on a hair?

51:54.885 --> 51:57.918
Beats me.

52:03.510 --> 52:05.046
Oh right,

52:05.046 --> 52:08.426
the Deputy Manager Son's wife was
scary yesterday, huh?

52:08.426 --> 52:11.050
She showed up because he wouldn't answer.

52:11.050 --> 52:13.519
She thinks he's involved
with Deputy Manager Jung.

52:13.519 --> 52:17.036
That's rough for her. She works nonstop.

52:17.036 --> 52:20.048
I kind of get it, though.

52:20.048 --> 52:23.095
Couples barely see each other at night.

52:23.095 --> 52:25.753
But coworkers are together all day.

52:25.753 --> 52:30.249
More in common, more to talk about.

52:30.249 --> 52:33.126
It gets to you.

52:33.126 --> 52:34.586
I wouldn't like it either.

52:34.586 --> 52:39.479
Still, there's a limit.
She's basically paranoid.

52:42.427 --> 52:44.898
She's famous.

52:44.898 --> 52:46.862
[Food Brand Planning Team]

52:46.862 --> 52:49.241
If we go like this,
Executive Kang will tear us apart.

52:49.241 --> 52:52.565
This is exactly what we agreed on.
Why does it keep changing?

52:52.565 --> 52:55.062
There's no clear focus.

52:55.062 --> 52:57.715
It's not about local competitors.

52:57.715 --> 53:00.439
I told you,
we need to focus on global expansion.

53:00.439 --> 53:03.668
They're just coworkers. Not an affair.

53:03.668 --> 53:06.330
- Huh?
- You don't remember?

53:08.127 --> 53:10.797
Let's analyze all companies under 1 billion.

53:10.797 --> 53:13.169
- We need everything.
- Got it.

53:13.169 --> 53:16.321
But how many registrations...

53:16.321 --> 53:18.807
Well... yeah.

53:21.671 --> 53:25.364
Hey! Over here!

53:30.081 --> 53:32.947
- Alright, everyone's here?
- Yes.

53:32.947 --> 53:36.670
We've got a major task.

53:36.670 --> 53:38.601
Straight from the top.

53:38.601 --> 53:40.327
From the top?

53:40.327 --> 53:44.024
So drop everything and handle this first.

53:44.024 --> 53:46.214
There's a criminal angle,

53:46.214 --> 53:49.312
and if it gets out, it'll blow up in the press.

53:49.312 --> 53:54.218
So we handle it quietly, clean and discreet.

53:54.218 --> 53:56.551
Got it?

53:56.551 --> 53:58.042
What is it?

53:58.042 --> 54:00.842
[Audit on site]
[Thank you for your cooperation]

54:01.909 --> 54:03.747
So, there are poppies here?

54:03.747 --> 54:07.325
Hey, keep your voice down.

54:07.325 --> 54:11.164
The security guard found one
while clearing the flower bed.

54:11.164 --> 54:13.170
Not the decorative kind.

54:13.170 --> 54:15.665
There might be more planted,

54:15.665 --> 54:18.035
so we handle it quietly
before it becomes an issue.

54:18.035 --> 54:20.419
Got it?

54:20.419 --> 54:24.570
A pharma company with poppies...

54:24.570 --> 54:26.824
Hey, did you eat one?

54:26.824 --> 54:28.971
Don't go picking random stuff
just because it's free.

54:28.971 --> 54:32.133
Come on, just find them already.

54:39.206 --> 54:40.238
Hello?

54:40.238 --> 54:44.948
I'm Deputy Manager Son's wife.
Did you check? The hair?

54:44.948 --> 54:46.972
We'll send the results by email.

54:46.972 --> 54:50.605
I'm in the middle of something,
so I'll hang up.

55:02.672 --> 55:05.066
Yes?

55:05.066 --> 55:08.223
You said you'd call right away.

55:08.223 --> 55:11.768
It's Deputy Manager Jung, right?

55:13.006 --> 55:15.697
So what happens to them now?

55:15.697 --> 55:17.662
The company should handle this strictly...

55:17.662 --> 55:21.179
Enough already!

55:21.179 --> 55:23.537
There's nothing going on.

55:23.537 --> 55:25.928
They're just working.

55:25.928 --> 55:28.647
They're together right now?

55:28.647 --> 55:29.931
Did you see them?

55:29.931 --> 55:34.490
Ma'am, don't do this.

55:34.490 --> 55:40.093
You should see a doctor. This is paranoia!

55:53.261 --> 55:56.007
You've got crap on you.

56:04.024 --> 56:05.958
Gosh.

56:14.670 --> 56:16.271
Rehearsal's in the main conference room, huh?

56:16.271 --> 56:18.275
Yeah. I told the team we're heading in.

56:18.275 --> 56:20.615
Hold on.

56:26.554 --> 56:28.867
Thanks.

57:15.092 --> 57:17.843
At least you bloom,

57:17.843 --> 57:20.762
in this dull office.

57:42.331 --> 57:45.737
Oh, Ki Jun. Heading out?

57:48.942 --> 57:52.039
I read your report on Son Myeong Su.

57:52.039 --> 57:53.679
That's really all?

57:53.679 --> 57:56.523
You're sure there's no affair?

57:56.523 --> 57:58.363
No.

57:58.363 --> 58:00.680
I can't be certain about something
between two people.

58:00.680 --> 58:02.557
There's no solid evidence.

58:02.557 --> 58:06.050
Based on what we checked,
there's nothing there.

58:07.540 --> 58:09.854
I like that you don't jump to conclusions.

58:09.854 --> 58:14.667
But since it's between two people,
shouldn't we dig a little deeper?

58:16.319 --> 58:18.063
- Hello.
- Hello.

58:18.063 --> 58:20.150
- Oh, Food Brand Team, right?
- Yes.

58:20.150 --> 58:24.643
- Working late? Hang in there.
- Hello.

58:25.715 --> 58:28.665
Where are Deputy Manager Son and Jung?

58:28.665 --> 58:31.845
They're prepping for a PT.
We're grabbing dinner.

58:31.845 --> 58:33.906
I see.

58:33.906 --> 58:38.543
How do you know all of us?
You really are "God Joo."

58:38.543 --> 58:39.575
"God Joo?"

58:39.575 --> 58:42.769
You see everything and know everything.

58:42.769 --> 58:46.046
Is that what they say? No way.

58:46.046 --> 58:48.090
"God Joo?"

58:48.090 --> 58:51.389
I know your team's working
on something important.

58:51.389 --> 58:52.440
Alright.

58:52.440 --> 58:55.193
You've been working late,
so God Joo's treating tonight.

58:55.193 --> 58:57.610
Something nice and expensive.

58:57.610 --> 59:00.563
You're amazing! God Joo!

59:00.563 --> 59:04.473
I'll send it up for everyone.
Head back upstairs.

59:04.473 --> 59:07.966
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

59:12.243 --> 59:16.501
- Keep it up.
- Thank you.

59:20.292 --> 59:23.271
- You should rewrite the report.
- What?

59:23.271 --> 59:27.613
Maybe I really am God Joo. Nice nickname.

59:33.935 --> 59:37.139
Want to run it again?

59:37.139 --> 59:39.839
Yes, sir.

59:43.550 --> 59:45.943
But...

59:50.579 --> 59:52.878
run what?

59:58.155 --> 01:00:00.809
This?

01:00:20.674 --> 01:00:23.704
What do you mean? Rewrite the report?

01:00:23.704 --> 01:00:25.541
You'll find out tomorrow.

01:00:25.541 --> 01:00:28.947
Or maybe... tonight.

01:01:15.243 --> 01:01:17.500
Are you okay?

01:01:17.500 --> 01:01:20.473
What about you?

01:01:20.473 --> 01:01:23.326
What the...

01:01:43.257 --> 01:01:45.684
Ma'am?

01:01:58.439 --> 01:02:00.099
What?

01:02:00.099 --> 01:02:02.698
Paranoid?

01:02:04.875 --> 01:02:07.752
Why is everyone coming at me?

01:02:07.752 --> 01:02:11.865
I'm not the crazy one. They are!

01:02:15.920 --> 01:02:18.583
I'll kill them!

01:03:29.120 --> 01:03:31.358
He's the pride of our team.

01:03:31.358 --> 01:03:33.335
Oh, you're the team's pride.

01:03:33.335 --> 01:03:34.636
Why is she being so shameless?

01:03:34.636 --> 01:03:39.971
If everyone were like you,
this place would be a lot better.

01:03:39.971 --> 01:03:43.058
Don't be an idiot.

01:03:43.058 --> 01:03:44.741
Get the job done right this time.

01:03:44.741 --> 01:03:48.014
Basement Level 4, Section F.

01:03:48.014 --> 01:03:49.945
- We need to catch them.
- Catch them?

01:03:49.945 --> 01:03:51.451
How do we even catch that?

01:03:51.451 --> 01:03:54.535
Ethics? Are you a cop or a judge?

01:03:54.535 --> 01:03:56.493
You hate Joo In Ah that much?

01:03:56.493 --> 01:03:57.944
Should I just quit?

01:03:57.944 --> 01:04:00.993
If you want out of Audit,
you should've said so.

01:04:00.993 --> 01:04:04.142
Instead of talking behind my back.
